commit_message:
RBD:Remove inappropriate exception handling in flush()

os_brick/initiator/linuxrbd.py
---------------------------
def flush(self):
    try:
        self._rbd_volume.image.flush()
    except AttributeError: -->this exception handling is not need.
        LOG.warning("flush() not supported in this version of
librbd")
---------------------------
Now ceph rbd driver has been supporting flush.
rbd.py
-------------------
def flush(self):
    """
    Block until all writes are fully flushed if caching is enabled.
    """
    ret = self.librbd.rbd_flush(self.image)
    ......
-------------------
librbd.c
-------------------
  int Image::flush()
  {
    ImageCtx *ictx = (ImageCtx *)ctx;
    tracepoint(librbd, flush_enter, ictx, ictx->name.c_str(),
ictx->snap_name.c_str(), ictx->read_only);
    int r = librbd::flush(ictx);
    tracepoint(librbd, flush_exit, r);
    return r;
  }
------------------
Change-Id: I1ef3605712efa910e15d5cf27a5bcf42c351c409

